Currently on the [Importing Users|https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/AOD/Importing+Users] page there are 2 queries which copy the tables contents to CSV files.

If we from support try to import those files as they are, the import tool errors out due to an incorrect CSV header. So we always end up having to manually updating the files.
So I suggest the following queries instead:
*users.sql*{noformat}copy (SELECT user_name AS "Username", first_name AS "First Name", last_name AS "Last Name", email_address AS "Email Address", credential AS "Password" FROM cwd_user) to '/tmp/users.csv' csv header;{noformat}
*group_memberships.sql*{noformat}copy (SELECT DISTINCT child_name AS "Username", parent_name AS "Groupname" FROM cwd_membership) to '/tmp/group_memberships.csv' csv header;{noformat}

